Because yesterday, statements against the plan were repeated among both Republicans and Democrats.
"It is clear that Washington will not hear your voice," said Republicans Scott Garrett, a member of the House Financial Committee.
"Yes, we have serious financial problems.
Yes, there are solutions.
But there is nothing that would benefit taxpayers. "
Brad Sherman, a Democrat representative who runs a small congressional group called the skeptical faction, presents things differently, but comes to the same conclusion.
"Four hundred excellent economists, including three Nobel Prize winners, have written to us to ask Congress not to hurry and to look carefully at which route he chose," said Sherman yesterday.
At the same moment in Europe, they understood once again that this is a global crisis.
