The highest price increase occurred in August 2008 in the leather product and footwear manufacturing sector (2.8%), mainly due to an increase of 4,6% in the production of bags and straps and 2,5% in the monthly price increase in footwear production.
The higher price levels of plastic and chemical raw materials have resulted in a significant monthly increase in the prices of the chemical, product and industry (1.6%).
