The price decrease occurred in the sectors of textiles, textile products (2,5%) and electrical machinery and apparatus (0,3%).
In the other processing sectors, the rate of price increase was between 0,6% and 9.1%.
Prices have increased by 10,2% over the last year in the manufacturing industry as a whole.
The prices in the electricity, gas, steam and water sectors were 18,7% higher than those of one year ago.
In August, domestic sales showed the highest monthly price increase (0,7%) in the production of capital goods.
Prices in the consumer product sector increased by 0,3% and in the energy and downstream sectors did not change as compared to the previous month.
In August 2008, the highest price increase compared to the same month of the previous year was observed in energy and downstream sectors (16.8%).
In the sectors producing consumer goods, we measured an increase of 6,8% in prices and a decrease of 1,4% in investment prices.
The export sales prices of the industry in forint increased by 1,1% in August compared to the previous month and decreased by 3,9% in 12 monthly comparisons.
